name: DPW8-Scatter
description: This is similar to the traditional DPW approach for transonic flow on a static geometry. This group will concentrate on identifying the reasons for data scatter that was observed in DPW-VII.

name: DPW8-Static-Deform
description: Fluid-structure interactions will be calculated and studied in detail. This group will be comprised of individuals in both DPW and AePW communities with significant collaboration leading up to the final workshop.

name: DPW8-Buffet
description: This group seeks to identify nature of pre- and post-buffet flight regimes with unsteady CFD analysis. Simulations will be performed on both experimentally-measured deformations and with coupled fluid/structure interactions. Members of the DPW and AePW communities will be involved.

name: DPW8-Wind-Tunnel
description: This group seeks to understand the impact of the wind-tunnel environment when compared to free-air CFD, in particular both forces and moments as well as surface pressures.

name: DPW8-Plotting
description: Plotting scripts for Drag and Aeroelastic Prediction Workshops
